(Core Explanation) Tj
T*
(The central focus in Immunity is body defenses, antibodies, and vaccination. A strong) Tj
T*
(explanation should show the idea clearly, connect it to prior knowledge, and then walk) Tj
T*
(through the method students are expected to use whenever they meet this topic in) Tj
T*
(classwork or examination questions.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Worked Understanding) Tj
T*
(A good classroom illustration for Immunity is explaining how a vaccine prepares the) Tj
T*
(immune system. When students can talk through that kind of example slowly and correctly,) Tj
T*
(they usually find it much easier to transfer the same reasoning to new questions.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Why Students Find It Difficult) Tj
T*
(One frequent problem in Immunity is thinking antibiotics work against viruses. Students) Tj
T*
(also struggle when they try to memorize final answers without understanding the steps) Tj
T*
(that make the answer valid. Clear explanations, careful checking, and repeated guided) Tj
T*
(practice reduce this difficulty.) Tj
